Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20Act%2C%202023.%20The%20petitioners%20particularly%20challenged%20the%20amendment%20that%20removed%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20topmost%20judge%20from%20the%20panel%20to%20select%20election%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20act%20replaces%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(Conditions%20of%20Service%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20Transaction%20of%20Business)%20Act%2C%201991.%20It%20provides%20for%20the%20appointment%2C%20salary%2C%20and%20removal%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Election%20Commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20selection%20panel%20is%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20has%20just%20one%20opposition%20member.%20It%20also%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20petitioners%20highlighted%20%E2%80%93%20violates%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20last%20year%20that%20Election%20Commission%20members%20be%20selected%20by%20a%20panel%20that%20is%20not%20dominated%20by%20the%20government%20so%20as%20to%20ensure%20its%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2014%2C%20this%20three-member%20selection%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-led-panel-appoints-ex-ias-officers-gyanesh-kumar-sukhbir-singh-sandhu-as-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Eappointed%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20former%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%20officers%20%E2%80%93%20Gyanesh%20Kumar%20and%20Sukhbir%20Singh%20Sandhu%20%E2%80%93%20as%20election%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-refuses-to-stay-election-commissioners-act-dropping-cji-from-selection-panel-252982%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20hearing%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Vikas%20Singh%20and%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20highlighted%20the%20violationg%20of%20the%20constitution%20bench%20judgment%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnoop%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EBaranwal%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20and%20the%20hurry%20displayed%20by%20the%20search%20committee%20in%20the%20recent%20appointments%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20Justice%20Khanna%20questioned%20Bhushan%20on%20the%20grounds%20on%20which%20he%20had%20challenged%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20they%20have%20been%20appointed%2C%20elections%20are%20on%20corner%E2%80%A6it%20is%20a%20question%20of%20balance%20of%20convenience.%20There%20are%20no%20allegations%20against%20persons%20appointed%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judge%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhushan%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20an%20independent%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Advocates%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%20and%20Sanjay%20Parikh%20also%20vouched%20for%20the%20harm%20this%20act%20would%20cause%20to%20the%20democratic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20notes%3A%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20this%20was%20met%20with%20resistance%20from%20the%20bench%2C%20which%20cautioned%20the%20senior%20counsel%20to%20not%20pass%20such%20statements.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20arguments%20would%20be%20examined%20but%20did%20not%20pause%20the%20act%20at%20this%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20told%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20that%20the%20names%20seen%20by%20the%20selection%20committee%20could%20have%20been%20examined%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20slowly.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20SG%20Mehta%20argued%20that%20the%20committee%20had%20considered%20two%20people%20in%20a%20process%20that%20started%20in%20February%2C%20and%20that%20the%20formulation%20of%20the%20committee%20was%20not%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20ensured%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20pointed%20to%20a%20disparity%20in%20the%20time%20given%20for%20the%20names%20to%20be%20considered.%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quotes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%201%