ce%20grains%20meant%20%3Cem%3EDanda%20Kattna%3C%2Fem%3E%20pooja%20for%20auspicious%20activities%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peculiar%20thing%20about%20Oraon%20paintings%20is%20that%20mud%20forms%20the%20main%20base%20due%20to%20the%20availability%20of%20various%20types%20of%20soils.%20The%20community%20creates%20different%20shades%20of%20black%2C%20brown%20and%20red%20from%20the%20soil.%20Green%20and%20white%20colours%20are%20made%20from%20leaves%20and%20rice%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumanti%20says%20she%20adds%20glue%20to%20the%20colours%20so%20that%20it%20sticks%20to%20the%20canvas.%20To%20date%2C%20she%20and%20the%20people%20from%20her%20village%20have%20not%20used%20acrylic%20or%20synthetic%20colours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20mentions%20two%20reasons%20for%20this%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20accessibility%20and%20cost%20came%20in%20the%20way%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20natural%20colours%20are%20a%20very%20important%20part%20of%20our%20identity.%20Our%20ancestors%20were%20confined%20to%20villages%2C%20so%20they%20made%20natural%20colours%20on%20their%20own%20and%20took%20pride%20in%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColours%20that%20come%20from%20the%20soil%20are%20seen%20as%20sacred%2C%20she%20informs.%20The%20elders%20of%20the%20house%20perform%20a%20brief%20ritual%2C%20praying%20for%20an%20obstacle-free%20search%20for%20the%20right%20soil.%20While%20red%20and%20brown%20soils%20were%20readily%20accessible%2C%20finding%20black%20ones%20was%20challenging%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20ancestors%20would%20have%20to%20dig%20in%20forests%20to%20find%20the%20black%20soil.%20The%20rarity%20factor%20makes%20the%20soil%20so%20important%20in%20our%20culture.%20Besides%2C%20these%20three%20colours%20are%20used%20in%20all%20our%20%3Cem%3Epujas%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20date.%20According%20to%20a%20legend%2C%20Mahadev%20and%20Parvati%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20told%20our%20ancestors%20to%20use%20these%20colours%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20colours%2C%20the%20primary%20themes%20also%20remain%20intact%20in%20the%20Oraon%20paintings.%20Mostly%2C%20the%20paintings%20depict%20community%20life%20%E2%80%94%20including%20their%20dance%2C%20customs%2C%20forest%20deities%20and%20festivals.%20The%20making%20can%20take%20up%20to%2010%20to%2015%20days%20due%20to%20the%20layered%20process.%20Each%20layer%20has%20to%20dry%20before%20the%20second%20layer%20is%20completed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20the%20paintings%2C%20Sumanti%20uses%20her%20fingers%20and%20cloth%20(for%20dabbing)%20even%20though%20the%20use%20of%20a%20brush%20is%20slowly%20penetrating%20the%20community%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20mud%20and%20fingers%20are%20our%20USP%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20factors%20are%20what%20makes%20art%20so%20much%20more%20valuable%20and%20personal.%20The%20paintings%20do%20not%20preach%20or%20tell%20how%20one%20should%20live.%20Instead%2C%20it%20depicts%20Oraon%E2%80%99s%20culture%20most%20honestly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CArt%20is%20a%20lifelong%20teacher.%20It%20has%20taught%20me%20to%20be%20fair%20towards%20myself%20and%20make%20the%20best%20of%20my%20circumstances.%20It%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20despite%20the%20harshness%20of%20life%2C%20financial%20burdens%2C%20incomplete%20dreams%20and%20frustrated%20days%2C%20it%20is%20okay.%20Every%20time%20I%20paint%2C%20it%20shows%20me%20the%20genuine%20merit%20of%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20960px)%20100vw%2C%20960px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FPhoto-credit-Sumanti-Devi-1710330421.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sumanti%20demonstrating%20her%20art%20to%20the%20participants%20of%20Samvaad.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FPhoto-credit-Sumanti-Devi-1710330421.jpeg%20